The `playProgressionReplay` function is already implemented in `/Users/backlit/Documents/code/chordessy/neural-arpeggiator/src/battle.js:872-881`:

```javascript
playProgressionReplay(progression) {
  if (!this.bridge || !this.bridge.audio) return;

  progression.chords.forEach((symbol, index) => {
    this.time.delayedCall(index * 400, () => {
      let midiNotes = C.chordToMidiNotes(symbol);
      this.bridge.audio.playChord(midiNotes, '4n');
    });
  });
}
```

Implementation matches requirements:
- ✅ Uses `audio.playChord()` to replay each chord
- ✅ Sequential playback with ~400ms gaps (`index * 400`)
- ✅ Musical payoff for progression completion